projects.description:
Programming language used: C#/XNA/DirectX shader
• Reconstructing a 3D landscape from a 2D height map, with customized color maps for the landscape and the functionality to navigate in the 3D landscape with the mouse;
• Shading and texturing of a 3D subject in presence of moving random lights with varying color.

profile_positions.description:
Supervisors: dr. Karma Dajani, prof. Michel Vellekoop, MSc. Geeske Vlaming.
The project was “Multivariate Asset Pricing”, and the main tasks were:
 • MatLab programming and Monte–Carlo simulations;
 • Model building and reconstruction;
 • Model fitting and parameter optimization;
 • Quantitative data analysis.
The results of this project (including MatLab codes) are described in the final Master thesis (available at the link below).

Programming Language: Matlab.
